Description: Production-candidate Web MIDI phase-distortion synthesiser and Turing machine firmware for Music Thing Modular Workshop Computer.
Name: C1ZZL3
Language: C++ (Pico SDK)
Creator: Adrian Vos
Instagram: https://instagram.com/professeur_whom
Version: 0.6
Status: Released but still Beta testing
Editor: https://soveda.github.io/CozmikC1zzl3/web-midi/editor/
tags:
  - synthesiser
  - phase-distortion
  - oscillator
  - turing-machine
  - sequencer
  - envelope
  - web-midi
  - usb-midi
  - 1v-oct

manual: |
  C1ZZL3 is a CZ-inspired phase-distortion oscillator card with a second mirrored
  oscillator for detune, ring modulation, and CZ-style noise/grit. It includes
  USB MIDI note input, USB MIDI host mode for class-compliant controllers on
  2025 Workshop Computer hardware, and a browser Web MIDI editor for custom
  envelope slots.

  This production candidate appears to be at the practical processing limit for
  the RP2040 card format with the current oscillator, envelopes, Web MIDI custom
  slots, USB MIDI device/host support, ring/noise, detune, Turing mode, CV
  outputs, and LED feedback. Turing MIDI output and synth-mode Turing clock
  persistence are intentionally absent because hardware testing showed those
  additions could cause lockups at maximum settings.

  Switch middle is the main PD synth voice. Main controls pitch, X controls
  phase-distortion amount, and Y controls waveform morph. Audio/CV In 1 adds
  1V/oct pitch. CV In 1 adds phase-distortion amount, CV In 2 adds wave control,
  and Audio In 2 is unused.

  Hold the switch down from middle to edit performance settings: Main controls
  oscillator 2 detune, X edits ring modulation, and Y edits noise/grit. Ring and
  noise start neutral after reset. If the card starts with the switch down,
  ring/noise editing is locked until the switch has first left down.

  Switch up opens the Turing machine. Main controls mutation, X controls length,
  and Y controls clock speed. Pulse In 1 is external clock. CV Out 1 carries
  stepped Turing CV, CV Out 2 carries smoothed Turing CV, Pulse Out 1 carries
  the main Turing pulse, and Pulse Out 2 carries an alternate bit pulse. CV In 1
  and CV In 2 add clamped phase-distortion and wave modulation in Turing mode.

  When leaving Turing mode, the last Turing CV and pulse values are held. The
  Turing clock does not continue running in synth mode. Tap tempo has been
  removed; Y is the only internal Turing clock-speed control.

  Hold the switch down during startup to enter envelope preset select. Factory
  presets are followed by any saved custom Web MIDI slots. LED 6 marks the
  custom bank and LEDs 1-3 show the custom slot number.

  The Web MIDI editor can load and save up to eight custom envelopes, set ring,
  noise, and MIDI input channel, and audition envelopes in the browser. Factory
  presets are never overwritten by SysEx. Custom names are stored by the browser;
  the card stores custom envelope shapes.

panel:
  inputs:
    - id: AudioIn1
      name: Audio/CV In 1
      description: 1V/oct pitch modulation in PD synth mode
    - id: AudioIn2
      name: Audio/CV In 2
      description: Unused in this production candidate
    - id: CVIn1
      name: CV In 1
      description: Adds phase-distortion amount in synth and Turing modes
    - id: CVIn2
      name: CV In 2
      description: Adds wave control in synth and Turing modes
    - id: PulseIn1
      name: Pulse In 1
      description: External Turing clock in switch-up mode
    - id: PulseIn2
      name: Pulse In 2
      description: Triggers the selected envelope and oscillator sync in synth mode when an active preset is selected
  outputs:
    - id: AudioOut1
      name: Audio Out 1
      description: Oscillator 1 in synth mode; self-playing stepped oscillator 1 in Turing mode
    - id: AudioOut2
      name: Audio Out 2
      description: Oscillator 2 in synth mode; self-playing stepped oscillator 2 in Turing mode
    - id: CVOut1
      name: CV Out 1
      description: Scaled stepped Turing CV; held at last value outside Turing mode
    - id: CVOut2
      name: CV Out 2
      description: Smoothed Turing CV; held at last value outside Turing mode
    - id: PulseOut1
      name: Pulse Out 1
      description: Main Turing pulse; held at last value outside Turing mode
    - id: PulseOut2
      name: Pulse Out 2
      description: Alternate Turing bit pulse; held at last value outside Turing mode

controls:
  knobs:
    - when: { z: middle }
      main:
        name: Main
        description: Oscillator pitch over octave-based range; uses pickup when returning from Turing mode
      x:
        name: X
        description: Phase-distortion amount; CV In 1 adds modulation; uses pickup when returning from Turing mode
      y:
        name: Y
        description: Waveform morph; CV In 2 adds modulation; uses pickup when returning from Turing mode

    - when: { z: down, gesture: hold }
      main:
        name: Main
        description: Oscillator 2 detune
      x:
        name: X
        description: Ring modulation amount with soft pickup
      y:
        name: Y
        description: Noise/grit amount with soft pickup

    - when: { z: up }
      main:
        name: Main
        description: Turing mutation/lock amount; centre is most random and extremes are more locked
      x:
        name: X
        description: Turing sequence length, 2 to 16 steps; briefly displays length as binary on LEDs
      y:
        name: Y
        description: Internal Turing clock speed

    - when: { startup: switch-down }
      main:
        name: Main
        description: Select factory or saved custom envelope preset
      switch:
        name: Switch Down
        description: Short press exits preset select; long hold saves selected preset to flash

  leds:
    - when: { z: middle }
      display: list
      items:
        - id: LED0
          name: LED 1
          description: Phase-distortion amount
        - id: LED1
          name: LED 2
          description: Waveform morph position
        - id: LED2
          name: LED 3
          description: Oscillator 2 level
        - id: LED3
          name: LED 4
          description: Ring modulation amount
        - id: LED4
          name: LED 5
          description: Noise/grit amount
        - id: LED5
          name: LED 6
          description: Lights while switch is held down

    - when: { z: up }
      display: list
      items:
        - id: LED0
          name: LED 1
          description: Low bit 0 of Turing pattern
        - id: LED1
          name: LED 2
          description: Low bit 1 of Turing pattern
        - id: LED2
          name: LED 3
          description: Low bit 2 of Turing pattern
        - id: LED3
          name: LED 4
          description: Pulse In 1 state
        - id: LED4
          name: LED 5
          description: Turing sequence length
        - id: LED5
          name: LED 6
          description: Flashes on every Turing clock step

    - when: { startup: envelope-select }
      display: binary
      items:
        - id: LED0
          name: LED 1
          description: Factory preset bit 0 or custom slot bit 0
        - id: LED1
          name: LED 2
          description: Factory preset bit 1 or custom slot bit 1
        - id: LED2
          name: LED 3
          description: Factory preset bit 2 or custom slot bit 2
        - id: LED3
          name: LED 4
          description: Factory preset bit 3
        - id: LED4
          name: LED 5
          description: Factory preset bit 4
        - id: LED5
          name: LED 6
          description: Custom bank marker for saved custom slots

presets:
  envelopes:
    - id: 0
      name: Off
    - id: 1
      name: Pluck
    - id: 2
      name: Double pluck
    - id: 3
      name: Bounce
    - id: 4
      name: Bell
    - id: 5
      name: Brass
    - id: 6
      name: Strings
    - id: 7
      name: Reverse swell
    - id: 8
      name: Evolving digital
